a_0.formal problem:
theorem
fixes x :: real
assumes h0 : "x = 36 / 7"
shows  "floor x = 5"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 Evaluate $\left\lfloor\frac{36}{7}\right\rfloor$. The final Answer is 5
 ### Proof
 $\left\lfloor\frac{36}{7}\right\rfloor=\left\lfloor 5 \frac{1}{7} \right\rfloor=\boxed{5}.$
 *)

theorem
fixes x :: real
assumes h0 : "x = 36 / 7"
shows  "floor x = 5"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer
a_0.informal problem: What is the greatest integer less than or equal to the fraction $\frac{36}{7}$? The final answer is 5.
